    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1966-10-19T07:30:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1966-10-19T07:30:00-05:00" n="276"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d276">
                <head>276. Telegram From the <gloss type="from">Embassy in Vietnam</gloss> to the
                        <gloss type="to">Department of State</gloss>
                    <note n="1" type="source" xml:id="d276fn1">Source: Department of State, Central
                        Files, <gloss target="#t_POL1">POL</gloss> 27 VIET S. Secret; <gloss
                            target="#t_Exdis1">Exdis</gloss>. Repeated to Canberra and Wellington
                        and passed to the White House, <gloss target="#t_DOD1">DOD</gloss>, and
                            <gloss target="#t_CIA1">CIA</gloss>.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>Saigon</placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian"
                            when="1966-10-19T12:30:00+00:00">October 19, 1966,
                        1230Z</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>8835. Ref: Saigon 7630.<note n="2" xml:id="d276fn2">
                        <ref target="#d258">Document 258</ref>.</note> Subject: <gloss
                        target="#t_GVN1">GVN</gloss> national reconciliation program.</p>
                <list>
                    <label>1.</label>
                    <item>
                        <persName corresp="#p_Thieu1">Thieu</persName> and <persName
                            corresp="#p_Ky1">Ky</persName> informed me today that they are prepared
                        to go ahead with national reconciliation program as discussed at our October
                        3 meeting.<note n="3" xml:id="d276fn3">See <ref target="#d258">Document
                                258</ref>.</note> They will make a general reference to the program
                        at Manila and will follow up with a proclamation on November 1.</item>
                    <label>2.</label>
                    <item>They are in agreement with us on need to expand <gloss
                            target="#t_ChieuHoi1">Chieu Hoi</gloss> program and to make a concerted
                        effort to win over <gloss target="#t_VC1">VC</gloss> cadre at all levels.
                        General <persName>Tri</persName>, Minister of Information and <gloss
                            target="#t_ChieuHoi1">Chieu Hoi</gloss>, is now actively engaged in
                        working out program and will be coordinating closely with US agencies.<note
                            n="4" xml:id="d276fn4">
                            <persName corresp="#p_LHC1">Lodge</persName> outlined his view of the
                            components of such a program in telegram 8958, October 20. <persName
                                corresp="#p_KH1">Kissinger</persName> outlined a program of national
                            reconciliation in a 9-page paper prepared with <persName>Daniel
                                Davidson</persName> of <gloss target="#t_FE1">FE</gloss> and
                            forwarded to <persName corresp="#p_LHC1">Lodge</persName> on October 19.
                            Frank Sieverts of <gloss target="#t_SS1">S/S</gloss> forwarded a copy to
                                <persName corresp="#p_KNB1">Katzenbach</persName> on November 1
                            under cover of a memorandum stating that it was the “key memorandum” for
                            a proposal for national reconciliation on which <persName
                                corresp="#p_BWP1">William Bundy</persName> and <persName
                                corresp="#p_HWA1">Harriman</persName> were working. (Both in
                            Department of State, Central Files, <gloss target="#t_POL1">POL</gloss>
                            27 VIET S)</note>
                    </item>
                    <pb facs="0799" n="763" xml:id="pg_763"/>
                    <label>3.</label>
                    <item>
                        <persName corresp="#p_Thieu1">Thieu</persName> reiterated <gloss
                            target="#t_GVN1">GVN</gloss> view that they cannot deal with <gloss
                            target="#t_VC1">VC</gloss> as a political entity, but only as an
                        internal security problem involving individuals or groups who will be given
                        opportunity to return to the fold. In regard to the amnesty, he said, the
                            <gloss target="#t_VC1">VC</gloss> will comprise two groups: those who
                        may wish to return to <gloss target="#t_NVN1">NVN</gloss>, and those who may
                        wish to stay. The latter will be handled through national reconciliation
                        program.</item>
                </list>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_LHC1">
                            <hi rend="strong">Lodge</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
